This paper deals with the development of a coding system to classify the causes of emergency room visits based on clinical notes in free-text. The paper discusses the use of neural language models (NLM) and supervised learning techniques to achieve this goal. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of unsupervised generative pre-training, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the processing of electronic medical records, which could fall under the categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
